===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[knob]] or [[disc]] that is passed through a [[loop]] or ([[buttonhole]]), serving as a [[fastener]]. {{defdate|from the mid-13th c.}}
#* {{quote-book|year=1898|author={{w|Winston Churchill (novelist)|Winston Churchill}}
|title={{w|The Celebrity}}|chapter=1
|passage=I liked the man for his own sake, and even had he promised to turn out a celebrity it would have had no weight with me. I look upon notoriety with the same indifference as on the '''buttons''' on a man's shirt-front, or the crest on his note-paper.}}
#: {{usex|April fastened the '''buttons''' of her overcoat to keep out the wind.|lang=en}}
# A mechanical device meant to be [[press]]ed with a finger in order to open or close an electric circuit or to activate a mechanism.
#: {{usex|Pat pushed the '''button''' marked "shred" on the blender.|lang=en}}
# {{context|graphical user interface|lang=en}} An [[on-screen]] control that can be [[select]]ed as an [[activator]] of an attached function.
#: {{usex|Click the '''button''' that looks like a house to return to your browser's home page.|lang=en}}
# {{context|US|lang=en}} A [[badge]] worn on clothes, fixed with a [[pin]] through the fabric.
#: {{usex|The politician wore a bright yellow '''button''' with the slogan "Vote Smart" emblazoned on it.|lang=en}}
# {{context|botany|lang=en}} A [[bud]].
#: {{rfquotek|Shakespeare}}
# {{context|slang|lang=en}} The [[clitoris]].
# {{context|curling|lang=en}} The center ([[bullseye]]) of the [[house]].
# {{context|fencing|lang=en}} The soft circular tip at the end of a [[foil]].
# {{context|poker|lang=en}} A plastic disk used to represent the person in last [[position]] in a poker game; also ''dealer's '''button'''''.
# {{context|poker|lang=en}} The player who is last to act after the flop, turn and river<!--but not preflop-->, who possesses the button.
# A [[raise]]d [[pavement]] [[marker]] to further indicate the presence of a pavement marking painted [[stripe]].
# {{context|South Africa|slang|lang=en}} A [[methaqualone]] [[tablet]] (used as a recreational drug).
# A piece of wood or metal, usually flat and elongated, turning on a nail or screw, to fasten something, such as a door.
# A [[globule]] of [[metal]] remaining on an [[assay]] [[cupel]] or in a [[crucible]], after [[fusion]].

====Usage notes====
For the senses 2 and 3, a button is often marked by a verb rather than a noun, and the button itself is called with the verb and ''button''. For example, a button to start something is generally called ''start button''.

